			<description><![CDATA[The results for the Air Force Common Admission Test (AFCAT 1 2026) have been released, and candidates can check their scores online. This article provides a step-by-step guide on how to download the scorecard, including direct links and important exam details. Don't miss out on your chance to access your results and learn about the recruitment opportunities available through this examination.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="https://naukrinama.com/static/c1e/client/99589/downloaded/5c72024b019b91260e6857e60e735d05.png" ><h2>AFCAT 1 2026 Results Released</h2>
 <p><br></p>
 <br>
 <p>The results for the Air Force Common Admission Test (AFCAT 1 2026) have been officially announced. Candidates who participated in the examination can check their results right away by visiting the official site at <a href="http://afcat.edcil.co.in">afcat.edcil.co.in</a> or by using the direct link available on this page. To access the scorecard, candidates must input their user ID and password.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Instructions for Downloading the Scorecard</h2>
 <p>Candidates can also retrieve their AFCAT 1 scorecard via a login link sent to their registered email address. Here are the steps to download the scorecard from the official website:</p>
 <br>
 <p>1. Navigate to the official website, afcat.edcil.co.in.</p>
 <br>
 <p>2. Locate the AFCAT 1 2026 login section.</p>
 <br>
 <p>3. Sign in by entering your user ID, password, and the captcha code provided.</p>
 <br>
 <p>4. The result will be displayed on the screen, allowing you to download it.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Direct Link to AFCAT 1 Result 2026</h2>
 <p><strong>AFCAT 1 Result 2026 Link:</strong></p>
 <br>
 <p><a href="https://cdn.digialm.com/EForms/configuredHtml/1258/96171/login.html">https://cdn.digialm.com/EForms/configuredHtml/1258/96171/login.html</a></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Exam Details</h2>
 <p>The Indian Air Force conducted the AFCAT on January 31, 2026, across various examination centers. The exam was held from 10:00 AM to 12:00 PM. This recruitment drive aims to fill positions in Flying, Ground Duty Technical, Ground Duty Non-Technical, and Flying roles under the AFCAT Entry and NCC Special Entry.</p>
 <br>]]></content:encoded>
