 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>New Delhi:</strong> For those aspiring to join the Indian Air Force, there is significant news. The Indian Air Force (IAF) has officially released the results for the Air Force Common Admission Test (AFCAT) 2026 today, Wednesday (March 11). Candidates who participated in this examination can now check their results. According to the department, candidates can view their scorecards on the official website.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>340 Vacancies to be Filled</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p>This year's recruitment drive aims to fill 340 vacancies for Group A Gazetted Officers. These positions are available in the Flying Branch, Ground Duty (Technical) Branch, and Ground Duty (Non-Technical) Branch.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Direct Link to Check AFCAT 2026 Results</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p>Steps to check the AFCAT 2026 results:</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Visit the official website at afcat.edcil.co.in.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Look for the link on the homepage indicating that the results for AFCAT-01/2026 have been announced.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> You will be redirected to the candidate login page.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Enter your registered email ID and password.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Your AFCAT 01/2026 scorecard will appear on the screen. Download it for future reference and keep multiple copies safe.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Details Included in the AFCAT 2026 Scorecard</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p>The AFCAT scorecard contains crucial information for candidates. It includes the candidate's full name, registration number, section-wise scores, total marks, the cutoff marks for that year, eligibility status for the next stage, and category-wise ranking details.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Next Step: Interview</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p>Candidates who pass the written examination must now prepare for the next stage. The Air Force Selection Board (AFSB) will conduct interviews, which are a critical part of the selection process. This interview assesses candidates' thinking, understanding, confidence, and leadership qualities. Only those who successfully navigate this stage will be referred for further consideration.</p>
