 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS) Recruitment 2026:</strong> The Government of India has initiated the recruitment process for the position of Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS). This announcement comes from the Animal Welfare Board of India (AWBI), which operates under the Ministry of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry, and Dairying. Individuals who have completed their 10th grade are eligible to apply for these MTS positions. Applications must be submitted offline, and candidates are required to send their forms to the specified address within 60 days from the date the recruitment advertisement appears in Employment News. The age criteria for applicants range from a minimum of 18 years to a maximum of 25 years, with age relaxation applicable as per Government of India guidelines.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Details on Vacancies and Salary</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Number of Positions Available:</strong><br> As per the notification from the Animal Welfare Board of India, there are three (03) Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS) positions available for direct recruitment. According to the Group 'C' Posts Recruitment Regulations, 2024, the pay scale for these positions falls under Level 1, which translates to a monthly salary ranging from ₹18,000 to ₹56,900. All eligible Indian citizens are encouraged to apply.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p>The number of vacancies may vary based on the official notification. The AWBI retains the authority to cancel or alter the recruitment process without providing any justification.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Application Process</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p>For detailed instructions and the application format, please visit <a href="http://www.awbi.gov.in">www.awbi.gov.in</a>. It is crucial to ensure that applications are complete and submitted on time, as incomplete or late submissions will not be considered. Careful attention is necessary when filling out the application, as even minor errors could lead to rejection.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Where to Send Your Application:</strong><br> Download the application form from www.awbi.gov.in, complete it with accurate information, and send it to the designated address.</p>
 <p></p>
