			<guid>https://naukrinama.com/results/bihar-board-class-12-results-2026-what-students-need-to/cid18349641.htm</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[The Bihar School Examination Board has concluded the Class 12 exams, and students are now waiting for the 2026 results. This article provides essential information on when the results will be announced, how to check them online, and details about the exam and answer key. Stay informed and prepared as the results approach.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="https://naukrinama.com/static/c1e/client/99589/downloaded/0ef5ad2a2b3bb447fdbe85dc44ff5042.png" ><h2>Bihar Board Class 12 Result 2026 Overview</h2>
 <p><br></p>
 <br>
 <p>The Bihar School Examination Board (BSEB) has successfully conducted the Class 12 examinations. Students who participated are now eagerly anticipating the announcement of their results. Many are curious about the exact date for the Bihar Board Class 12 Result 2026.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Typically, the BSEB reveals the result date a few days prior to the actual results. This announcement is usually made during a live press conference, where the board provides specific details about the timing of the results.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>How to Check Bihar Board Class 12 Results</h2>
 <p>Once the results are published, students can access them by visiting the official website at <a href="http://results.biharboardonline.com">results.biharboardonline.com</a>. By entering their credentials, students can view their results and download their scorecards. Additionally, results will be available via SMS.</p>
 <br>
 <p><strong>Steps to Download the Bihar Board Class 12 Result:</strong></p>
 <br>
 <p>1. Go to the official BSEB website.</p>
 <br>
 <p>2. Look for the 'BSEB Class 12 Result' link on the homepage, which will be activated once the results are out.</p>
 <br>
 <p>3. Click on the link, and a new page will prompt you to enter your roll number/roll code and name.</p>
 <br>
 <p>4. After submitting the required information, your result along with subject-wise marks will be displayed on your screen.</p>
 <br>
 <p>5. Don't forget to print your scorecard.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Exam Details and Answer Key</h2>
 <p>The Bihar Board Class 12 examinations took place from February 2 to February 13. The results will be provided in the form of mark sheets, which students must collect from their respective schools.</p>
 <br>
 <p>The answer key for the objective-type questions was released on March 1, containing correct answers for all subjects. An objection window was available until 5 PM on March 6, 2026.</p>
 <br>]]></content:encoded>
