			<link>https://naukrinama.com/government-jobs/exciting-job-openings-at-central-electronics-limited-apply/cid18353073.htm</link>
			<guid>https://naukrinama.com/government-jobs/exciting-job-openings-at-central-electronics-limited-apply/cid18353073.htm</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[Central Electronics Limited (CEL) is offering 34 job vacancies, including roles like Deputy Engineer and various managerial positions. The application process is open until March 14th, and candidates must meet specific eligibility criteria. With salaries ranging from ₹17,500 to ₹2,20,000, this is a prime opportunity for those seeking government employment. Interested applicants should visit the official CEL website to apply and ensure they submit their applications before the deadline. Don't miss out on this chance to advance your career!]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="https://naukrinama.com/static/c1e/client/99589/downloaded/a63102d58bd11acf65b21771358023d3.png" ><h2>Central Electronics Limited Recruitment Announcement</h2>
 <p><br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Individuals interested in securing a position within a Government of India enterprise should take note of a significant opportunity. Central Electronics Limited (CEL) has released a notification for 34 various roles, including that of Deputy Engineer. The online application window opened on February 11th and will close on March 14th. Candidates who meet the eligibility criteria and wish to apply should visit the official CEL website to submit their applications before the deadline to avoid missing out.</p>
 <br>
 <p>The available positions at CEL encompass a range of roles, such as Deputy General Manager (Electrical/Electronics), Deputy General Manager (Microwave), Deputy General Manager/Senior Technical Manager (Material Science), Deputy General Manager/Senior Manager (HR), and several Deputy Engineer roles in Software Development, Sales &amp; Marketing, Embedded Systems, and Material Science. Additionally, there are openings for Personnel Officer, Hindi Officer/Rajbhasha Adhikari on a contract basis, Management Trainee (Human Resources), Graduate Engineer Trainee (Computer Science), and various other positions.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Applicants are required to hold a BE/B.Tech/MBA/CA/ICWA/Graduation or Matriculation degree from a recognized institution, depending on the position applied for. Other eligibility criteria must also be satisfied.</p>
 <br>
 <p>The age limit for applicants ranges from 25 to 63 years as of January 31st, with age relaxation available for candidates from reserved categories.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Candidates who successfully register by the deadline will undergo a selection process that includes shortlisting, a written examination, a personal interview, and document verification. Salaries for selected candidates will vary between ₹17,500 and ₹2,20,000 per month, based on the specific role.</p>
 <br>
 <p>An application fee is required for submission, which is ₹1,000 for candidates in the General/EWS/OBC categories. However, this fee is waived for SC/ST/PwBD and ex-servicemen.</p>
 <br>
 <p>To apply online, candidates should visit the official CEL website, click on the application link for their desired position, fill in the necessary details, upload required documents, and pay the application fee according to their category. After verifying the information, candidates should submit the form and print a copy for their records.</p>
 <br>]]></content:encoded>
