			<title><![CDATA[Punjab Anganwadi Recruitment 2026: Apply for 6,110 Worker and Helper Positions]]></title>
			<link>https://naukrinama.com/government-jobs/punjab-anganwadi-recruitment-2026-apply-for-6110-worker-and/cid18349630.htm</link>
			<guid>https://naukrinama.com/government-jobs/punjab-anganwadi-recruitment-2026-apply-for-6110-worker-and/cid18349630.htm</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[The Punjab Social Security and Women and Child Development Directorate has reopened applications for over 6,000 Anganwadi worker and helper positions. Eligible candidates who have completed their 10th or 12th grade can apply online until March 11, 2026. This recruitment is exclusively for women residing in Punjab, with specific age and language requirements. The selection will be based on academic merit without a written exam. Interested applicants should act quickly to secure their chance at these vital community roles.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="https://naukrinama.com/static/c1e/client/99589/downloaded/b7e8a46c7906305c5d3cc8b099fb2d7d.png" ><h2>Punjab Anganwadi Recruitment 2026 Overview</h2>
 <p><br></p>
 <br>
 <p><strong>Punjab Anganwadi Recruitment 2026:</strong> A significant recruitment initiative has been launched for individuals interested in joining the Anganwadi workforce. The Punjab Social Security and Women and Child Development Directorate (SSWCD Punjab) has reopened applications for more than 6,000 positions for Anganwadi workers and helpers. The online application process commenced on February 25th on the official website. Interested candidates should apply promptly as the deadline approaches.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Eligibility Criteria for Punjab Anganwadi Recruitment</h2>
 <p>This recruitment is available for candidates who have completed their 10th or 12th grade from a recognized educational board. Therefore, those meeting these educational qualifications are encouraged to apply.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Key Details of Punjab Anganwadi Vacancies</h2>
 <p><strong>Punjab Anganwadi Vacancy 2026: Essential Information</strong><br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Recruiting Body: Punjab Social Security and Women and Child Development Directorate (SSWCD)<br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Position Titles: Anganwadi Worker and Helper<br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Total Positions: 6,110 (Anganwadi Workers - 1,316, Helpers - 4,794)<br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Application Deadline: March 11, 2026<br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Required Qualifications: 10th, 12th<br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Salary: As per government regulations</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Eligibility Requirements</h2>
 <p>To qualify for the Anganwadi Worker role, candidates must have completed their 12th grade from a recognized board. For the Helper position, a minimum of 10th grade is necessary.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Only female candidates are eligible to apply for these positions.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Applicants must possess proficiency in the Punjabi language.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Residency in Punjab is a prerequisite for applicants.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Candidates should be between 18 and 37 years old, with age relaxation available for those in reserved categories.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Application Process for Anganwadi Recruitment</h2>
 <p>To apply for the Anganwadi recruitment, follow these steps:</p>
 <br>
 <p>1. Visit the official Punjab Anganwadi website.</p>
 <br>
 <p>2. Locate the recruitment notification on the homepage.</p>
 <br>
 <p>3. Click on the 'Apply Online' link.</p>
 <br>
 <p>4. Register using your basic details.</p>
 <br>
 <p>5. Log in with your registration number and fill out the application form.</p>
 <br>
 <p>6. Provide all required information, including your name, parents' names, category, date of birth, age, educational qualifications, and address.</p>
 <br>
 <p>7. Submit the application fee and save a copy of your application form.</p>
 <br>
 <h2>Selection Process</h2>
 <p>Candidates will be selected based on their academic merit. There will be no written test or interview; however, selected candidates will be invited for an interview after the final selection.</p>
 <br>]]></content:encoded>
