 <br>
 <p>The deadline for submitting applications for the Combined Eligibility Test (AIIMS NORCET 10), organized by the All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS) in Delhi, is set for March 16th. Aspiring candidates who wish to secure government positions and meet the eligibility requirements are urged to complete their online applications promptly via the official AIIMS website.</p>
 <br>
 <p>Before proceeding with the application, candidates should verify their eligibility. To qualify for this recruitment examination, applicants must possess a B.Sc. (Hons.) Nursing or a B.Sc. Nursing degree from a recognized institution. Furthermore, candidates must be registered as a nurse and midwife with either the Indian Nursing Council or the respective State Nursing Council. A minimum of two years of experience in a hospital with at least 50 beds is also required.</p>
 <br>
 <p>In terms of age requirements, candidates must be at least 18 years old and not exceed 30 years of age. Age relaxation provisions apply to candidates from reserved categories, with the age limit calculated as of March 16, 2026.</p>
