			<description><![CDATA[The Uttar Pradesh Police Recruitment and Promotion Board (UPPRPB) is set to conduct the written exam for the UP Police Sub Inspector (SI) Recruitment 2025 on March 14th and 15th. With over 1.5 million candidates expected, the board will release admit cards on March 11th and 12th. Strict measures are in place to prevent cheating and paper leaks, with options for candidates to report any suspicious activities. Stay informed about the latest updates regarding this significant recruitment drive.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="https://naukrinama.com/static/c1e/client/99589/downloaded/3a1e2684ca6d8121451094a765db7832.png" ><h2>UP Police SI Recruitment 2025 Overview</h2>
 <p><br></p>
 <p><strong>UP Police SI 2025:</strong> The Uttar Pradesh Police Recruitment and Promotion Board (UPPRPB) has finalized the arrangements for the written examination of the UP Police Sub Inspector (SI) Recruitment 2025. Candidates can expect the release of their admit cards soon, specifically on March 11th and 12th. To ensure the integrity of the examination process, the UPPRPB has implemented stringent measures to deter cheating and prevent paper leaks.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Exam Schedule and Candidate Participation</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Exam Dates: March 14th and 15th</strong><br>The UPPRPB announced the recruitment notification for the UP Police SI in October 2025, inviting applications for 4,543 positions. The written exams are set to take place on March 14th and 15th at 1,090 locations throughout the state. An estimated 1,575,760 candidates are expected to participate in this examination.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Admit Card Availability</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Admit Card Download Dates: March 11th and 12th</strong><br>According to the UPPRPB, candidates can download their admit cards for the written exam on March 11th and 12th. Those scheduled for the exam on March 14th can access their admit cards on March 11th, while candidates taking the exam on March 15th can download theirs on March 12th. The admit cards will be available on the official UPPRPB website.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Measures Against Cheating</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Reporting Paper Leaks</strong><br>The UPPRPB has prohibited any discussions on social media regarding the written exam for the UP Police SI Recruitment 2025. To combat issues like paper leaks and cheating, the board has established strict protocols. Individuals can report any suspicious activities related to the exam by emailing satarkta.policeboard@gmail.com or messaging via WhatsApp at 9454457951. The UPPRPB assures that all reports will be kept confidential.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>]]></content:encoded>
