			<guid>https://naukrinama.com/government-jobs/central-bank-of-india-recruitment-2026-apply-for-counselor/cid18348116.htm</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[The Central Bank of India is inviting applications for two Counselor positions, with a deadline of March 13, 2026. Candidates aged between 45 and 65 with a graduate degree and computer skills can apply. The selection process includes an interview and document verification, offering a monthly salary of ₹25,000. Interested individuals should visit the official website for application details and further information.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="https://naukrinama.com/static/c1e/client/99589/downloaded/47fb591817a294aaaa9de707d8735b5d.png" ><h2>Central Bank of India Recruitment 2026 Overview</h2>
 <p><br></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Central Bank of India Recruitment 2026:</strong> The Central Bank of India has opened applications for two Counselor roles. Candidates interested in this opportunity should complete their application forms without delay. This is an excellent chance to join a government bank. The application deadline is set for March 13, 2026. The available positions include one Counselor for FLC Ahilyanagar and another for FLC Dhule. Applicants are required to hold a graduate degree from a recognized institution and must possess computer skills, including proficiency in MS Office, internet usage, and typing in the local language.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Age Requirements</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>What is the age limit?</strong><br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Candidates must be at least 45 years old to apply, with a maximum age limit of 65 years. Age relaxation will be provided for candidates belonging to reserved categories in accordance with government policies.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Selection Process</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>What is the recruitment process?</strong><br></p>
 <br>
 <p>Selection will be based on a personal interview and verification of documents. Successful candidates will receive a monthly salary of ₹25,000.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <h2>Application Steps</h2>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>What is the application process?</strong><br></p>
 <br>
 <p>To apply online, candidates should first navigate to the official website of the Central Bank of India.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p>The application link will be prominently displayed on the homepage. Click on it.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p>Fill in all required details accurately.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p>Upload necessary documents, including a photo and signature, ensuring they meet the specified size and format.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p>Review the application before submission.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>
 <p></p>
 <p>For further details, candidates are encouraged to consult the recruitment notification thoroughly.</p>
 <p></p>
 <br>]]></content:encoded>
